    "---\n",
    "# TASK 2: Applying BLEU and ROUGE Metrics"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2.1 BLEU Score Implementation & Example\n",
    "\n",
    "**BLEU (BiLingual Evaluation Understudy)** measures n-gram overlap between generated and reference text.\n",
    "\n",
    "Formula: `BLEU = BP × exp(Σ w_n log(p_n))` where:\n",
    "- `p_n` = precision of n-grams\n",
    "- `BP` = brevity penalty (penalizes short outputs)\n",
    "- `w_n` = weight for n-gram (typically 0.25 each for 1-4 grams)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Interpretation:**\n",
    "- 0.0-0.1: Catastrophic\n",
    "- 0.1-0.3: Poor\n",
    "- 0.3-0.5: Fair\n",
    "- 0.5-0.7: Good\n",
    "- 0.7-1.0: Excellent"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from collections import Counter\n",
    "import math\n",
    "\n",
    "def calculate_bleu(reference, candidate, n=4):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Calculate BLEU score manually for transparency.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Args:\n",
    "        reference: Reference text (string)\n",
    "        candidate: Generated text (string)\n",
    "        n: Maximum n-gram size (default 4)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "        dict with BLEU score and component scores\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    # Tokenize\n",
    "    ref_tokens = reference.lower().split()\n",
    "    cand_tokens = candidate.lower().split()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Calculate brevity penalty\n",
    "    ref_len = len(ref_tokens)\n",
    "    cand_len = len(cand_tokens)\n",
    "    brevity_penalty = 1.0 if cand_len >= ref_len else math.exp(1 - ref_len / cand_len) if cand_len > 0 else 0\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Calculate n-gram precisions\n",
    "    precisions = []\n",
    "    weights = [0.25, 0.25, 0.25, 0.25]  # equal weights for 1-4 grams\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for gram_size in range(1, n + 1):\n",
    "        # Extract n-grams\n",
    "        ref_ngrams = [tuple(ref_tokens[i:i+gram_size]) for i in range(len(ref_tokens)-gram_size+1)]\n",
    "        cand_ngrams = [tuple(cand_tokens[i:i+gram_size]) for i in range(len(cand_tokens)-gram_size+1)]\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Count matches (clipped by reference count)\n",
    "        ref_counts = Counter(ref_ngrams)\n",
    "        cand_counts = Counter(cand_ngrams)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        matches = sum(min(cand_counts[ngram], ref_counts[ngram]) for ngram in cand_counts)\n",
    "        total = max(len(cand_ngrams), 1)  # avoid division by zero\n",
    "        \n",
    "        precision = matches / total if total > 0 else 0\n",
    "        precisions.append(precision)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Calculate BLEU\n",
    "    log_sum = sum(weights[i] * math.log(p + 1e-10) for i, p in enumerate(precisions[:n]))\n",
    "    bleu_score = brevity_penalty * math.exp(log_sum)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return {\n",
    "        'BLEU': round(bleu_score, 4),\n",
    "        '1-gram_precision': round(precisions[0], 4),\n",
    "        '2-gram_precision': round(precisions[1], 4),\n",
    "        '3-gram_precision': round(precisions[2], 4),\n",
    "        '4-gram_precision': round(precisions[3], 4),\n",
    "        'brevity_penalty': round(brevity_penalty, 4),\n",
    "        'reference_length': ref_len,\n",
    "        'candidate_length': cand_len\n",
    "    }\n",
    "\n",
    "# Example 1: AI Ethics Text\n",
    "ref_1 = \"Despite the increasing reliance on artificial intelligence in various industries, human oversight remains essential to ensure ethical and effective implementation.\"\n",
    "cand_1 = \"Although AI is being used more in industries, human supervision is still necessary for ethical and effective application.\"\n",
    "\n",
    "bleu_result_1 = calculate_bleu(ref_1, cand_1)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=\"*70)\n",
    "print(\"BLEU SCORE EXAMPLE 1: AI Ethics\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*70)\n",
    "print(f\"\\nReference:\\n  {ref_1}\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nGenerated:\\n  {cand_1}\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nResults:\")\n",
    "for key, value in bleu_result_1.items():\n",
    "    print(f\"  {key:.<25} {value}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\n💡 Interpretation:\")\n",
    "print(f\"  BLEU Score: {bleu_result_1['BLEU']} → Fair (vocabulary overlap exists)\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Issue: Paraphrases penalized (e.g., 'artificial intelligence' vs 'AI')\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2.2 ROUGE Score Implementation & Example\n",
    "\n",
    "**ROUGE (Recall-Oriented Understudy for Gisting Evaluation)** measures recall of n-grams.\n",
    "\n",
    "Main variants:\n",
    "- **ROUGE-1** (unigrams): Good for coverage of key terms\n",
    "- **ROUGE-2** (bigrams): Captures word pairs, indicators of fluency\n",
    "- **ROUGE-L** (longest common subsequence): Measures word order similarity\n",
    "\n",
    "Formula: `ROUGE-N = Recall = (matching n-grams) / (total n-grams in reference)`\n",
    "\n",
    "Unlike BLEU (precision-focused), ROUGE focuses on recall — did we cover all important words?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def calculate_rouge_manual(reference, candidate):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Calculate ROUGE-1, ROUGE-2, and ROUGE-L scores manually.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    ref_tokens = reference.lower().split()\n",
    "    cand_tokens = candidate.lower().split()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    results = {}\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # ROUGE-1 (unigrams)\n",
    "    ref_unigrams = Counter(ref_tokens)\n",
    "    cand_unigrams = Counter(cand_tokens)\n",
    "    matches_1 = sum(min(cand_unigrams[token], ref_unigrams[token]) for token in cand_unigrams if token in ref_unigrams)\n",
    "    recall_1 = matches_1 / max(sum(ref_unigrams.values()), 1)\n",
    "    precision_1 = matches_1 / max(sum(cand_unigrams.values()), 1)\n",
    "    f1_1 = 2 * (precision_1 * recall_1) / (precision_1 + recall_1) if (precision_1 + recall_1) > 0 else 0\n",
    "    \n",
    "    results['ROUGE-1'] = {\n",
    "        'recall': round(recall_1, 4),\n",
    "        'precision': round(precision_1, 4),\n",
    "        'f1': round(f1_1, 4)\n",
    "    }\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # ROUGE-2 (bigrams)\n",
    "    ref_bigrams = [tuple(ref_tokens[i:i+2]) for i in range(len(ref_tokens)-1)]\n",
    "    cand_bigrams = [tuple(cand_tokens[i:i+2]) for i in range(len(cand_tokens)-1)]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    ref_bigrams_count = Counter(ref_bigrams)\n",
    "    cand_bigrams_count = Counter(cand_bigrams)\n",
    "    matches_2 = sum(min(cand_bigrams_count[bigram], ref_bigrams_count[bigram]) for bigram in cand_bigrams_count if bigram in ref_bigrams_count)\n",
    "    recall_2 = matches_2 / max(sum(ref_bigrams_count.values()), 1)\n",
    "    precision_2 = matches_2 / max(sum(cand_bigrams_count.values()), 1)\n",
    "    f1_2 = 2 * (precision_2 * recall_2) / (precision_2 + recall_2) if (precision_2 + recall_2) > 0 else 0\n",
    "    \n",
    "    results['ROUGE-2'] = {\n",
    "        'recall': round(recall_2, 4),\n",
    "        'precision': round(precision_2, 4),\n",
    "        'f1': round(f1_2, 4)\n",
    "    }\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return results\n",
    "\n",
    "# Example 2: Climate Change Text\n",
    "ref_2 = \"In the face of rapid climate change, global initiatives must focus on reducing carbon emissions and developing sustainable energy sources to mitigate environmental impact.\"\n",
    "cand_2 = \"To counteract climate change, worldwide efforts should aim to lower carbon emissions and enhance renewable energy development.\"\n",
    "\n",
    "rouge_result_2 = calculate_rouge_manual(ref_2, cand_2)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=\"*70)\n",
    "print(\"ROUGE SCORE EXAMPLE: Climate Change\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*70)\n",
    "print(f\"\\nReference:\\n  {ref_2}\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nGenerated:\\n  {cand_2}\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nResults:\")\n",
    "for rouge_type, scores in rouge_result_2.items():\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n  {rouge_type}:\")\n",
    "    for metric, value in scores.items():\n",
    "        print(f\"    {metric:.<20} {value}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\n💡 Interpretation:\")\n",
    "print(f\"  High ROUGE-1 recall: {rouge_result_2['ROUGE-1']['recall']} → Key terms covered\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Lower ROUGE-2: {rouge_result_2['ROUGE-2']['f1']} → Different phrasing/word order\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2.3 Limitations of BLEU & ROUGE\n",
    "\n",
    "**Why BLEU & ROUGE Fail on Creative/Context-Sensitive Text:**\n",
    "\n",
    "| Problem | Example | Impact |\n",
    "|---------|---------|--------|\n",
    "| **Paraphrase Insensitivity** | \"fast\" vs \"quick\" → no match | Low score despite semantic equivalence |\n",
    "| **Synonym Blindness** | \"automobile\" vs \"car\" → no match | Penalizes vocabulary variation |\n",
    "| **Word Order Rigidity** | \"car is red\" vs \"red car\" → limited credit | Ignores valid restructurings |\n",
    "| **Idioms & Expressions** | \"it's raining cats and dogs\" → no literal match | Fails on metaphor/idiom |\n",
    "| **Factual Correctness** | \"Paris is capital of Germany\" gets high score if tokens match | No semantic understanding |\n",
    "| **Domain Variation** | Medical domain: \"myocardial infarction\" vs \"heart attack\" → penalized | Ignores domain-specific synonyms |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Critical Examples:**\n",
    "1. **Creative Writing:** Poetry, storytelling → Multiple valid versions\n",
    "2. **Open-ended QA:** Same answer, different explanations\n",
    "3. **Machine Translation:** Idioms don't translate literally\n",
    "4. **Summarization:** Content preservation matters more than word overlap\n",
    "5. **Dialogue:** Fluency and relevance > exact word matching"
   ]
  },
