    "---\n",
    "# TASK 3: Perplexity Analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 3.1 Understanding Perplexity\n",
    "\n",
    "**Perplexity** measures how well a probability model predicts a sample.\n",
    "\n",
    "Formula: `Perplexity(M) = exp(-1/N Σ log P(w_i))`\n",
    "\n",
    "Where:\n",
    "- `N` = number of words\n",
    "- `P(w_i)` = probability the model assigns to word `i`\n",
    "\n",
    "**Intuition:** Perplexity is the \"effective vocabulary size\" — e.g., Perplexity=100 means the model is as confused as if choosing from 100 equally likely words.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Key Properties:**\n",
    "- Lower perplexity = Better model (more confident predictions)\n",
    "- Higher perplexity = Worse model (less confident)\n",
    "- Sensitive to probability calibration"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def calculate_perplexity(probabilities):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Calculate perplexity from word probabilities.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Perplexity = exp(-1/N * Σ log(p_i))\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    if not probabilities or len(probabilities) == 0:\n",
    "        return float('inf')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Calculate negative average log likelihood\n",
    "    neg_avg_ll = -sum(math.log(p + 1e-10) for p in probabilities) / len(probabilities)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Calculate perplexity\n",
    "    perplexity = math.exp(neg_avg_ll)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return perplexity\n",
    "\n",
    "# Example 3.1: Comparing two models\n",
    "print(\"=\"*70)\n",
    "print(\"PERPLEXITY COMPARISON: Model A vs Model B\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*70)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Model A: assigns 0.8 probability to \"mitigation\"\n",
    "model_a_probs = [0.8]  # Single word example\n",
    "perp_a = calculate_perplexity(model_a_probs)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Model B: assigns 0.4 probability to \"mitigation\"\n",
    "model_b_probs = [0.4]\n",
    "perp_b = calculate_perplexity(model_b_probs)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\nModel A: P('mitigation') = 0.8\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Log probability: {math.log(0.8):.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Perplexity: {perp_a:.4f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\nModel B: P('mitigation') = 0.4\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Log probability: {math.log(0.4):.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Perplexity: {perp_b:.4f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\n📊 Result:\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Model A Perplexity ({perp_a:.4f}) < Model B Perplexity ({perp_b:.4f})\")\n",
    "print(f\"  ✓ Model A is BETTER (lower perplexity = more confident predictions)\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\n💡 Interpretation:\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Model A correctly identified 'mitigation' with 80% confidence\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Model B is less certain, only 40% confidence\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Difference: {abs(perp_a - perp_b):.4f} perplexity points\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
